&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WOMENS &amp; CHILDRENS DIVISION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PAEDIATRIC UNIT &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PAEDIATRIC NEWLY QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;BAND 5 STAFF NURSE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RSCN / RN Child Essential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;24 hours per week (Internal rotation)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a highly motivated and enthusiastic Paediatric Nurse who enjoys working as part of an innovative and dynamic Paediatric Team? If so, we have an exciting opportunity for you at The Hillingdon Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the Shaping a Healthier Future reconfiguration of Paediatric services in North West London, the Paediatric unit at Hillingdon has gone through a major transformation and refurbishment, including the addition of four new ensuite cubicles and a teenage room in our Peter Pan’s wards new Wing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric inpatient ward at The Hillingdon Hospital consists of a 24-bedded general medical and surgical ward, which includes a level 1 POSCU, 6-bedded Paediatric Day Care Unit and a Paediatric outpatients department. Paediatric services at Hillingdon also consists of our award winning, dedicated diabetes team; Paediatric respiratory and allergy services; the Paediatric community nursing team; Paediatric A&amp;E department; neonatal unit and child development centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is highly motivated, enthusiastic and possesses excellent communication and interpersonal skills within a multi-disciplinary team to join our fantastic Paediatric department. If you are a passionate and caring paediatric nurse who is team oriented, patient focussed, and ready for new and exciting challenges to develop your career, there are many opportunities for you here at Hillingdon. We can offer a supportive environment to help you develop and consolidate new competencies and are committed to helping you realise your potential. Through personalised training and development plans, dedicated practice educators and generous study leave, we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional development tailored to your individual needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal rotation programme within the Women &amp; Children’s Division, Paediatric A&amp;E and Neonatal Unit. Other rotation options may be available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to undertake short courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal and External study days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
